title: Tommy Salami & the Rough Rockers - Final Performance “Here Comes My  Girl” & “You Have My Heart”
description:
Recorded on August 29, 2014 in Uxbridge, Massachusetts - this is the final performance of the legendary Folk-Rock Americana group “Tommy Salami and the Rough Rockers”, featuring a rare cover of the song “Here Comes My Girl”, originally written and recorded by Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers, for their 1979 album, “Damn the Torpedoes”. Following this is a clip of the bands signature original song, “You Have My Heart”, written by Tommy Salami and the Rough Rockers, for their unreleased EP of the same name. 

Tommy Salami and the Rough Rockers 
lineup that evening consisted of the following:

Michael Sartori - Lead and Rhythm guitars, Lead vocals
Jason McCutchen - Bass guitar, backup vocals
Zack Lenz - Hammond B3 organ, Piano, backup vocals
Joshua Pilling - lead and rhythm guitars
Zack Pfeffer - drums
Karl Helstrom - sound engineer 
Damon Tyler - manager
Peter Sartori - road crew
